name: Leveraging-Consensus-Algorithms-to-Optimize-Microservice-Systems
description: Leveraging Consensus Algorithms to Optimize Microservice Systems

name: langchain-llama3-Chroma-RAG-demo
description: This system implements a micro-microservice architecture, and uses vuetify+langchain+local large model+local vector database to build a demonstration of the RAG system.

name: Microservices-API-with-FastAPI
description: This repository contains a simple microservices architecture implemented using FastAPI. The system is designed to manage Products, Customers, and Orders through three independent microservices.

name: Microservice-Admin-Server
description: A Spring Boot-based admin server that provides a centralized dashboard for monitoring and managing microservices in a distributed system. It integrates with Spring Boot Actuator and other monitoring tools to track health, metrics, and system status.

name: distributed-microservices-platform
description: A microservices-based system with services for user management, inventory, payments, and notifications. Includes service discovery, circuit breakers, and gRPC communication.

name: Employee-Management-System
description: A Enterprise level microservices-based Employee Management System using Spring Boot, designed to streamline workforce management through comprehensive services, secure authentication, and advanced organizational insights.

name: flask_busline_gis_microservice
description: A Flask-based microservice for managing bus routes, bus stops, and schedules, using GIS technology for map-based visualization and efficient search. Provides APIs for route management, stop location search, and schedule display, enabling better public transportation system integration.

name: NT531.P11-Observability_Systems
description: This repository we use to store our resource about out project - Building a Observability system for a Microservices-Based Web Application on Kubernetes (EKS)

name: track-parcel-service
description: Microservices-based parcel tracking system with Telegram bot integration, message broker, and gRPC communication, designed for seamless parcel management and notifications.

name: Airline-Booking-Platform
description: A Flight Booking System with a microservices architecture, including booking, search, payment services, load balancing, API Gateway, and message queues for scalability and decoupled services.

name: Molecular.Js-FrameWork
description: This repository showcases a microservices architecture built using Moleculer.js and NATS for inter-service communication. It demonstrates the use of a scalable, event-driven design with features like service discovery, load balancing, and fault tolerance. Perfect for exploring distributed systems and modern backend development!

name: SeaFogWatch
description: SeaFogWatch is a real-time sea fog monitoring system using Himawari satellite data and machine learning. Its microservices architecture integrates Python-based deep learning models with a robust backend and frontend, providing accurate fog detection for maritime safety and weather forecasting. A cutting-edge solution for environmental monitoring.
